quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  69,9,And Pharaoh and those before him and the turned over cities (Sodom and Gomorrah) came with sinning
  69,10,"Then they disobeyed their Master's messenger, so He took them (into punishment), an increasing punishment"
  69,11,"Indeed when the water rose up, We carried you on the sailing ship (the Ark)"
  69,12,"So that We make it a reminder for you, and attentive ear to remember it"
  69,13,"So when the trumpet is blown, a single blow"
  69,14,and the earth and the mountains are lifted and crushed in a single blow
  69,15,Then on that day the event happens
  69,16,"and the sky splits, then on that day it (the sky) is weak"
  69,17,"and the angels are at its sides, and eight (angels) carry your Masterâ€™s throne above them"
  69,18,On that day you are presented (before God) and none of your secrets remains hidden
  69,19,"So, as for anyone who is given his book (of records) to his right hand, he says: here, read my book"
  69,20,indeed I thought that I come across my account
  69,21,Then he will be in a pleasant life
  69,22,in an excellent garden
  69,23,its bunches of fruits are nearby (within easy reach)
  69,24,"(They are told): eat and drink joyfully for what you sent in advance in the days gone by"
  69,25,"But anyone who is given his book to his left hand, he says: I wish I was not given my book"
  69,26,and I did not know what is my account
  69,27,I wish it was the end
  69,28,my wealth was of no use to me
  69,29,my power departed from me
  69,30,"(It will be said): take him and shackle him"
  69,31,then make him enter (and burn in) the hellfire
  69,32,then put him in a chain that its length is seventy cubits
  69,33,for indeed he would not believe in the great God
  69,34,and he would not encourage feeding the poor